# Alembic Migration Guide

This directory contains Alembic migration configuration for a single-database setup.

## Purpose

- Track schema changes over time
- Generate versioned migration files
- Apply or roll back database changes safely

## Folder Contents

```text
alembic/
|-- env.py
|-- script.py.mako
|-- versions/
`-- README
```

## Common Commands

Run these commands from the project root (the directory containing `alembic.ini`):

```bash
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "create users table"
alembic upgrade head
alembic downgrade -1
alembic current
alembic history
```

## Notes

- Ensure your database URL is configured correctly before running migrations.
- Review generated migration scripts before applying them in production.